column5: Has anybody  seen the 4" fillet knife?  I haven't seen any, maybe they only stocked the 5 and 9
The Lindsay store has about a dozen 9" knifes left and a few other items but no plano cases (I was just there)
I didn't know Dollarrama is worst than Shoppers or Tim's!  The Dollarrama at Kingsway plaza has 6' knives and frogs not the 1 behind Tims the one 500ft to east.

The Lindsay store has about a dozen 9" knifes left and a few other items but no plano cases (I was just there)  Thanks for the update on the Plano boxes! I should start calling around, maybe I'll get lucky and find a stash of them. Doubt it though.

I remember the last Dollarama item.. The $3 Plano box.. Long gone now!! If you are interested in these get them while you can.. Lol
That was a good one. I bought a case of them!
I bought a knockoff plano type there but the latches were sticky.  The stock in the different stores seems to vary quite a bit. I have gone looking for items posted here but not much luck.

I remember the last Dollarama item.. The $3 Plano box.. Long gone now!! If you are interested in these get them while you can.. Lol  I managed to grab more of those plano boxes last month.  Sweet score for only $3
Just a heads up, they sometimes have them at Walmart too in the sewing section, along with good beads for harnesses and even powerpro lol(my wife sews)
I pass a half dozen Dollarama stores just running my errands... I guess I will leave extra time when I can..
I picked up the knife about 2 weeks back at one of my local Dollarama's but they did not have those frogs at mine.
Thanks for the heads up. Rainy day, so hit the store. Grabbed 4 frogs. The 2 black ones are cool. They rattle, I had to hit 5 stores til I found the knife. It is very nice. Quality is very good.
I was told they have a 9" inch Shimano knife too at $4
I have the 6, really want a 4.

So I have been using my first knife for deboning chicken,trimming up pork loins and such. What a great knife for doing this. I have yet to use it on fish,as I haven't  caught  any since I purchased it. LOL  Took a wander in the same store I found my first and they had some 6" left, so grabbed another. At the back tool wall, they had the larger 9" one. Same price,$4. Had to get it, as I know it,s going to make a great roast and turkey carver.  If you like a sharp quality knife, I would advise grabbing these. Totally impressed.  The frog supply was pretty much history.
Huck 674 was hunting again!
I check the Grimsby store periodically for the Plano boxes with no luck. If anyone sees them in another store, please let me know. I'd like to buy another case of them. Thanks!
The majority of people who bought those plano cases were little girls who used them to store their loom bands.  If they sold so well, Dollarama should make a note and restock them more often.

I could use a few more Plano boxes but it isn't life or death.. My old ones have latches that are breaking off... I will give the frogs a test soon..
